is planning the first stage of modernization works in
northeastern  Brazil  to boost supplies to 28 municipalities,
BNAmericas said, citing a statement from the utility.  Initial works by Salvador-based Empresa Baiana de Aguas e
Saneamento SA, known as Embasa, to upgrade the Sao Francisco
water network including the city of Senhor do Bonfin are
budgeted at 480 million reais ($210 million), the news report
said, citing technical director Cesar Ramos. It said later works
would extend the water network in the city of Jacobina.  To contact the reporter on this story:
